  "texts": [
    "Through the classification, aggregation, and mapping of individual urban memory digital traces, we construct a dynamic, emotionally layered \"urban collective memory map\".",
    "This method not only meets the requirements of collective memory in terms of shareability, symbolism, and historical context but also overcomes the limitations of traditional oral history and survey methods, which are constrained by small sample sizes and slow updates.",
    "It provides a more sensitive and innovative spatial tool for urban space renewal, cultural heritage preservation, and the study of local identity.",
    "We selected Nanjing, the capital city of Jiangsu Province, China, as the subject of our analysis.",
    "Nanjing has a rich historical and cultural heritage, having been the capital of six ancient Chinese dynasties."
  ],
